pull t est
a bug in the parameter type of DBmotifs in EnrichmentScore is resolved and the network file is changed for this component
the network file is changed to include the newly added EnrichmentScores component
the problem with escape characters in WM file names is resolved by enclosing the filename in quatation mark in motevo command
The problem in the drmaa library for submiting bulk jobs in EnrichmentScore component is resolved

The EnrichmentScore component is added that fits the parameters for each motif and finally calculate and report the std and mean values of the enrichment score for each motif. This component runs over a bulk of motifs, mainly de novo motifs and DB motifs. There is only one problem with Drmaa running bulk jobs or job arrays

A filename mistake in RefineMotif component is resolved, and the network file as well as the config files are updated to include the WEBLOGO path which is located at group directory under software folder
network file is changed for FilterWM component
some few bugs in RefinedMotif compenent is resolved mainly regarding to the weblogo calling and motif generation

motevo_ver1.03 is added to the scripts. This version of motevo defines a key in its parameter file which is called refinedwmfile. The value of this paramter tells motevo to what filename write the resulted refined motif/WM.
The modified weblogo-3.4 is added to the scripts. In addition a minor changes is being made in MotifRefinement component to use the modified weblogo in order to generate the motifs.
the network file is being changed by adding the MotifRefinement, FittingBetaPrior parameters and EnrichmentScore to the current pipeline

fixings in RepeatsOut component

changes in RepeatsOut and RunMotevo, and plus adding a new component which is called FitBackgroundPriorAndBeta. This new component fits the prior background and the beta over the test_pool sequences. Note that the sequences must be single species -- no alignment, and in the MotEvo parameter file we are setting background frequency to uniform -- 0.25 for each nucleotide. There is no use of UFE as well.
the RunPhylogibbs component is changed to autmatically perform WM trimming.
